14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 3A O.S. 2021, Section 267, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 267. For purposes of this act, the organization elected
18 by horsemen that was, in 2003, providing representation for
19 participating Thoroughbred horsemen at meets restricted to
20 Thoroughbred horses only shall be the official representative of all
21 Thoroughbreds participating in live race meets conducted by an
22 organization licensee. The organization elected by horsemen that
23 was, in 2003, providing representation for the breeds participating
24 in mixed-breed racing shall be the official representative of all
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB1089 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 non- Thoroughbreds participating in live race meets conducted by an
2 organization licensee.
3 Organization licensees shall negotiate and covenant with the
4 official representative for each breed participating at any race
5 meeting as to the conditions for each race meeting, the distribution
6 of commissions and purses not governed by statutory distribution
7 formulae, simulcast transmission and reception, off-track wagering,
8 all matters relating to welfare, benefits and prerogatives of the
9 participants in the meet, and any other matter required as a matter
10 of law or necessity. During race meets at which there is more than
11 one official representative for horsemen, each official
12 representative association shall designate an equal number of
13 horsemen to serve on a single committee that will periodically meet
14 with the organization licensee to discuss and facilitate track
15 management operations. Any participating horsemen may with written
16 notice filed with the track's horsemen's bookkeeper elect to opt out
17 of representation by the above-referenced organizations. In the
18 event more than fifty percent (50%) of the total participating
19 horsemen for a single breed opt to be excluded, the Oklahoma Horse
20 Racing Commission may determine that an election be held among all
21 participating horsemen of that breed to designate an alternate
22 representative organization.
23 The official horsemen's representative organizations, and any
24 breed organizations receiving funding as a result of this act, shall
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB1089 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)
1 prov ide the Commission annually with a complete financial accounting
2 for the use of all funds received pursuant to this act. The
3 official horsemen's representative organization shall administer the
4 benevolence program for participants in each live race meeting and a
5 complete accounting of those funds along with the guidelines for
6 administration and determination of eligibility for the benevolence
7 program are subject to approval by the Commission.
8 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
9 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON BUSINESS AND INSURANCE
April 10, 2025 - DO PASS
